pancy indicators, unit counts, or volume-driven business metrics (e.g., room nights sold)\n\nClassification / Business Metadata\n\nOptional qualitative or categorical attributes (e.g., market classifications or performance tier labels)\n\nNot every metric is mandatory across the dataset, but the schema supports a broad set of financial reporting inputs.\n\nData Structure Characteristics\n\nEach row uniquely identifies:\n\n(property_id/property_name) × (calendar month)\n\n\nColumns include a mixture of:\n\nNumeric (currency values, counts, ratios)\n\nText descriptors\n\nDerived computed fields\n\nThere are no hierarchical subtotals or cross-property rollups stored in the table; aggregation for analysis is expected to be performed programmatically.\n\nIntended Analytical Use\n\nThis schema supports:\n\nProperty-level financial trend analysis\n\nCross-property benchmarking\n\nAutomated forecasting, variance, or KPI reporting\n\nNatural language query interpretation, with mapping to known entities, metrics, and period structures\n\nIt is designed to provide a consistent foundation for SQL query generation, BI tooling, and automated reasoning.	[{"id": "field_1763930691069_0", "name": "hotel_name", "type": "text", "required": true, "description": "", "displayLabel": "Hotel"}, {"id": "field_1763930691069_1", "name": "reporting_currency", "type": "text", "required": true, "description": "", "enumOptions": ["INR", "USD"], "displayLabel": "Reporting Currency"}, {"id": "field_1763930691069_2", "name": "period_type", "type": "enum", "required": true, "description": "", "enumOptions": ["month", "quarter", "year"], "displayLabel": "Period Type"}, {"id": "field_1763930691069_3", "name": "period_start_date", "type": "date", "required": true, "description": "", "displayLabel": "Period Start Date"}, {"id": "field_1763930691069_4", "name": "room_revenue", "type": "currency", "required": false, "description": "", "displayLabel": "Room Revenue"}, {"id": "field_1763930691069_5", "name": 